 :tx/rationale "C9-HONEST-ASSESSMENT: Full review of what was built vs what was promised. WHAT WORKS: (1) Kernel primitives are correct and well-tested: agent_observation_groups, find_agreement_clusters, extract_observation_links, link_datoms, detect_stagnation — all 19 tests pass with zero regressions across 1665 total. (2) Seed scoring formula includes corroboration and is backward-compatible by construction. (3) Convergent findings section now renders in build_orientation() when multi-agent data exists. (4) Stagnation detection wired into methodology_gaps. WHAT DOES NOT WORK IN PRACTICE: The live store has all 226 audit observations from the same agent identity (braid:user default). Even though 4 independent audit subagents produced them, they all flowed through braid observe with the same --agent flag. find_agreement_clusters correctly returns empty because there is only 1 distinct AgentId. This is not a code bug — it is an integration gap. The agent identity must be set at observation creation time using --agent flag, not inferred after. WHAT NEEDS TO HAPPEN NEXT: (1) When running parallel audit agents, each agent should use a distinct --agent identity: braid observe '...' --agent audit-agent-1. (2) The existing 226 observations could be retroactively tagged by inspecting which subagent session created them, but this requires store-level entity updates. (3) The convergent findings rendering in seed is correct and will activate the moment the store has observations from 2+ distinct agents. REVISED RATINGS: Correctness 8/10, Steering 5/10 (primitives exist but single-agent data limits utility), Accretiveness 6/10 (will be fully accretive once multi-agent workflow uses distinct --agent flags), Axiological alignment 7/10 (architecture is right, wiring is right, data gap is the bottleneck)."
